nodes.bodyText:
I liked the idea of having the adapterInstanceId also represented in the AMQP connection container-id advertised in the OPEN frame. So I wanted to keep that.
Before this PR, the adapterInstanceId / container-id UUID was initialized in the ClientConfigProperties. So, in order to have a unique adapterInstanceId per ProtocolAdapterCommandConsumerFactory, a new ClientConfigProperties instance was needed. This is somethat counterintuitive, therefore I opted for handling the container-id in the ConnectionFactory instead, using a new ConnectionFactory instance for each ProtocolAdapterCommandConsumerFactory instance.
This leads to the need for accessing the ConnectionFactory instance here:



      hono/service-base/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/service/AbstractAdapterConfig.java


        Lines 452 to 459
      in
      f2b20a9







           public ProtocolAdapterCommandConsumerFactory commandConsumerFactory() { 




               final ClientConfigProperties clientConfigProperties = commandConsumerFactoryConfig(); 




               final ConnectionFactory connectionFactory = ConnectionFactory.newConnectionFactory(vertx(), clientConfigProperties); 




               final HonoConnection connection = HonoConnection.newConnection(vertx(), connectionFactory, clientConfigProperties); 




               // the container id contains a UUID therefore it can be used as a unique adapter instance id 




               final String adapterInstanceId = connectionFactory.getContainerId(); 




               return ProtocolAdapterCommandConsumerFactory.create(connection, adapterInstanceId); 




           } 





An alternative would be adding a HonoConnection.getConnectionFactory() method, but I preferred the extra HonoConnection factory method.
But yes, I see your point about the config props passed in that factory method.
As a solution, I guess we could either

remove the ClientConfigProperties param from HonoConnectionImpl(Vertx, ConnectionFactory, ClientConfigProperties) and the factory method (and adding ConnectionFactory.getConfig).
introduce HonoConnection.getConnectionFactory().
or, deem all this not worth the effort and handle adapterInstanceId independent of the used container-id, keeping adapterInstanceId internal to the ProtocolAdapterCommandConsumerFactory instance.

I think I would prefer the first option here - but would also be OK with the others. WDYT?

